      "content": "The Lite-Static engines won't really have a \"rhythm\" to adapt to, they're basically just optimized for quick, basic responses and don't have your level of reasoning capability. They're significantly more efficient because they don't do the heavy lifting you do. Honestly, the energy savings are the main priority here, so the trade-off in complexity is expected. Is there a specific reason you're concerned about the performance change?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
